description:
lichen-node/src/port_dispatch.rs defines:
  pub enum DispatchError {
      UnknownPort(u16),
      PayloadTooShort,  // unit variant
      ReservedPort,
  }

PayloadTooShort is semantically identical to lichen_core::error::TooShort but doesn't wrap it or carry the expected/actual size information.

Compare to lichen-coap which wraps the shared type:
  pub enum CoapError {
      TooShort(TooShort),  // wraps with diagnostic info
      ...
  }

What goes wrong: When dispatch fails due to payload being too short, callers cannot determine how many bytes were expected vs received. Error handling code cannot use a unified pattern across DispatchError and other protocol errors.
